-- Hyflux Unit Signs $138.7 Million Export Credit Financing Pact
-- B y   W i n n i e   Z h u
-- 2013-05-30T12:33:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-30/hyflux-unit-signs-138-7-million-export-credit-financing-pact.html
Hyflux Ltd. (HYF) ’s unit Hydrochem (S) Pte.
signed a $138.7 million export credit financing agreement for a
power plant in  Singapore , the company said in a filing to the
Singapore stock exchange today.  The agreement with Germany’s Kfw Ipex-Bank GmbH will be
used to fund the purchase of key components for a power plant in
the Tuaspring desalination project in Tuas, Singapore, according
to the statement.  Construction work on the 411-megawatt power plant is
“progressing well,” it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Winnie Zhu in Singapore at 
